<head><title>JSPX - XHTML Example</title></head><body><h1>JSPX - XHTML Example</h1><hr/>
    This example uses JSPX to produce an XHTML 
    document suitable for use with many devices, like mobile phones, televisions, PDAs, smart watches, etc.
    <p/>
    JSPX lets you create dynamic documents in a pure XML syntax compatible with existing XML tools.  The XML syntax in JSP 1.2 was awkward and
    required &lt;jsp:root&gt; to be the root element of the document.
    This is no longer the case in JSP 2.0.
    <p/>
    This particular example uses a tag file to produce the DOCTYPE and namespace declarations to make the output of this page a valid XHTML Basic document.
    <p/>
